HEADWORD: Homaloidal
<hw>Hom`a*loid"al</hw> <pr>(-loid"⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>"omalo`s</grk> even + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>Flat; even; -- a term applied to surfaces and to
spaces, whether real or imagined, in which the definitions, axioms, and
postulates of Euclid respecting parallel straight lines are assumed to
hold true.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homarus</ent>⟦br⟧
